1. Baskı
Adam’s Diary and other stories
https://imageserver.kitapyurdu.com/select.php?imageid=9625987&isWatermarked=true
2019-09-04
 7,80
Mark Twain’s famous novels Tom Sawyer and Huckleberry Finn have long been hailed as major achievements, but the father of American literature also made his mark as a master of the humorous short story. Some of the tales he wrote over the course of his lengthy career are gathered here and Twain’s inimitable wit, his nimble plotting, and his unerring insight into human nature are on full display in these wonderfully entertaining stories.
127
 Mark Twain
